  "title": "Manager",
  "description": "<p>Core Responsibilities of a Massage Shop Manager</p><p>Operations Management: Responsible for daily shop operations, including staff scheduling, hygiene, equipment maintenance, fire safety, and financial oversight.</p><p>Strategy Execution: Understand and implement company strategies, turning headquarters’ goals into actionable shop-level plans.</p><p>Team Management: Recruit, train, and evaluate massage therapists and service staff, ensuring consistent service standards and boosting team morale.</p><p>Customer Service: Analyze customer needs, optimize service processes, handle complaints, and enhance customer satisfaction and loyalty.</p><p>Goal Setting: Develop annual, quarterly, and monthly targets, break them down into individual tasks, and monitor execution.</p><p>Product and Promotion Management: Oversee product inventory, display, and promotional activities to increase sales.</p><p>Market Expansion: Analyze market and competition, propose innovative service approaches, and maintain relationships with the community, peers, and cross-industry partners.</p><p>Training and Motivation: Organize onboarding programs, conduct one-on-one coaching, delegate responsibilities, and motivate staff for growth.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
